text: Yana Petrenko (born 30 July 1990) is a Kazakhstani female volleyball player. She is a member of the Kazakhstan women's national volleyball team and played for Zhetysu Almaty in 2011. She was part of the Kazakhstani national team at the 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship in Japan, and at the 2011 FIVB World Grand Prix in Italy. She participated at the 2018 Asian Games where her team scored 25-11, 22-25, 25-15, 19-25, 16-14 against the Philippines. ==Clubs== * Zhetysu Almaty (2010) ==References== ==External links== *FIVB profile Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Kazakhstani women's volleyball players Category:Sportspeople from Nur-Sultan Category:Volleyball players at the 2018 Asian Games
